{
  "info": {
    "name": "Eterna Labs Order Execution Engine",
    "description": "Complete API collection for Order Execution Engine. See POSTMAN_GUIDE.md for detailed instructions.\n\n**Quick Start:**\n1. Start server: `npm run dev`\n2. Test Health Check first\n3. Create an order (Market/Limit/Sniper)\n4. Copy orderId from response\n5. Connect WebSocket: `ws://localhost:3000/api/orders/{orderId}/ws`\n\n**Note:** WebSocket requires Postman v10+ or use wscat CLI tool.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "1. Health Check",
      "request": {
        "method": "GET",
        "header": [],
        "url": {
          "raw": "{{base_url}}/health",
          "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
          "path": ["health"]
        },
        "description": "Verify server is running. Should return status: ok"
      },
      "response": []
    },
    {
      "name": "2. Orders",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "Create Market Order",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Save orderId to collection variable for WebSocket testing",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (response.orderId) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('order_id', response.orderId);",
                  "        console.log('Order ID saved:', response.orderId);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"market\",\n  \"tokenIn\": \"SOL\",\n  \"tokenOut\": \"USDC\",\n  \"amount\": \"100\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a market order that executes immediately at best available price.\n\n**Response:** Returns orderId - save this for WebSocket connection.\n\n**WebSocket URL:** `ws://localhost:3000/api/orders/{orderId}/ws`"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Limit Order",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Save orderId to collection variable for WebSocket testing",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (response.orderId) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('order_id', response.orderId);",
                  "        console.log('Order ID saved:', response.orderId);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"limit\",\n  \"tokenIn\": \"SOL\",\n  \"tokenOut\": \"USDC\",\n  \"amount\": \"100\",\n  \"limitPrice\": \"1.05\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a limit order that waits for price condition.\n\n**Condition:** Executes when currentPrice >= limitPrice (for selling)\n**Timeout:** 30 minutes (configurable)\n\n**Response:** Returns orderId - save this for WebSocket connection.\n\n**WebSocket Events:** pending → waiting_for_trigger → routing → building → submitted → confirmed"
          },
          "response": []
        },
        {
          "name": "Create Sniper Order",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "exec": [
                  "// Save orderId to collection variable for WebSocket testing",
                  "if (pm.response.code === 200) {",
                  "    const response = pm.response.json();",
                  "    if (response.orderId) {",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('order_id', response.orderId);",
                  "        console.log('Order ID saved:', response.orderId);",
                  "    }",
                  "}"
                ],
                "type": "text/javascript"
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              {
                "key": "Content-Type",
                "value": "application/json"
              }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\n  \"type\": \"sniper\",\n  \"tokenIn\": \"NEW_TOKEN\",\n  \"tokenOut\": \"USDC\",\n  \"amount\": \"100\"\n}",
              "options": {
                "raw": {
                  "language": "json"
                }
              }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/orders/execute",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "orders", "execute"]
            },
            "description": "Creates a sniper order that waits for token availability (launch detection).\n\n**Behavior:** Polls DEX quotes every 1 second until token becomes available, then executes immediately.\n\n**Response:** Returns orderId - save this for WebSocket connection.\n\n**WebSocket Events:** pending → scanning_launch → routing → building → submitted → confirmed"
          },
          "response": []
        }
      ],
      "description": "Order creation endpoints. Each returns an orderId that should be used for WebSocket connection."
    }
  ],
  "variable": [
    {
      "key": "base_url",
      "value": "http://localhost:3000",
      "type": "string"
    },
    {
      "key": "order_id",
      "value": "",
      "type": "string",
      "description": "Auto-filled from order creation responses. Use for WebSocket URL: ws://localhost:3000/api/orders/{{order_id}}/ws"
    }
  ]
}


